  "text": "Age was not significantly related to QOL. Severity of bowel symptoms was significantly related to both total HRQOL and each of the subscales. With respect to illness perceptions, only the Brief IPQ dimensions measuring consequences, identity and emotional representation were significantly related to HRQOL. None of the Pearson's correlations between the independent and the mediator variables exceeded the 0.80 multicollinearity threshold suggested by field [CITATION_1] . The correlation coefficients are reported in Table 2 .",
